  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed roof extension by reason of its inappropriate detailed design, prominent siting, scale, visibility, massing, bulk and height would result in a dominant and discordant addition to the host building, wider terrace setting whilst disrupting the unaltered and the consistent front and rear roofline within this stretch of terraced buildings and fail to preserve or enhance the character or appearance of the Upper Street (North) conservation area. The proposed development would erode the existing rhythm of the roofs on the terrace along this Cobble Mews and would be seen as a harmful feature when observed from both the public and private realms.  The proposed development is therefore contrary to the NPPF (2021), Policies D1 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017) & Islington Local Plan Policy PLAN 1 (Site appraisal, design principles and process), Policy DH1 (Fostering innovation and conserving and enhancing the historic environment) 2023 and guidance contained within Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines 2002."
